  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ecuador Earthquake 2016 Disaster Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Giving Children Hope has collected items to send four 40&apos; shipping containers to those in need after the earthquake in Ecuador. 
Sean Lawrence, Executive Director, went to Ecuador to access the needs, bring medical supplies, and vet distribution streams. He worked to secure the proper distribution of the aid being sent among our network of partners there. 
We hope to send another container of recovery and rebuilding supplies including:
Large Tents- 5 person with floors and mosquito netting
Flashlights
Halogen Lights
LED lights
Radios
Generators
NEW Sleeping Bags
Water Purification Systems
NEW Construction Equipment- gloves, hard hats, etc. 
If anyone wishes to donate these items they must be NEW. Ecuador is beginning the rebuilding stage and these are their most requested items.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hundreds have been killed, thousands injured and many more are displaced from their homes in Ecuador after the 7.8 earthquake hit on Saturday April 16th, 2016. Giving Children Hope has sent 5 containers of lifesaving relief supplies including water, toothbrushes and toothpaste, diapers of all sizes, new clothing, vitamins, preserved foods, and bandages. Giving Children Hope is working with the local Ecuadorian Consulate in Los Angeles to determine the greatest needs.</narrative>
  </description>
